params.contentTypes: A bitwise OR of the ABI formats accepted by the caller.

approve(bytes32,address,bool).details: This method only sets the approval status for msg.sender's nodes.

params.approved: Whether the `delegate` has approval to modify records for `msg.sender`'s `node`.
params.node: The namehash `node` whose permissions are being updated.

params.owner_: The permissioned address initialized as the `owner` in the `Ownable` context.
params.registrarController_: The address of the RegistrarController contract.
params.reverseRegistrar_: The address of the ReverseRegistrar contract.

params.interfaceID: The EIP 165 interface ID to check for.

returns._0: The address that implements this interface, or 0 if the interface is unsupported.

params.delegate: The address of the `delegate` whose permissions are being checked.
params.node: The namehash `node` whose permissions are being checked.
params.owner: The address of the name owner.

returns._0: `true` if `delegate` is approved to modify `msg.sender`'s `node`, else `false`.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

returns.x: The X coordinate of the curve point for the public key.
returns.y: The Y coordinate of the curve point for the public key.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.contentType: The content type of the ABI

params.implementer: The address of a contract that implements this interface for this node.

params.x: the X coordinate of the curve point for the public key.
params.y: the Y coordinate of the curve point for the public key.

params.registrarController_: The address of the new RegistrarController contract.

params.reverseRegistrar_: The address of the new ReverseRegistrar contract.

params.value: The text data value to set.

params.interfaceID: the ERC165 iface id being checked for compliance

returns._0: bool Whether this contract supports the provided interfaceID

params.key: The text data key to query.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

ABI(bytes32,uint256).notice: Returns the ABI associated with an BNS node. Defined in EIP205.

addr(bytes32).notice: Returns the address associated with an BNS node.

approve(bytes32,address,bool).notice: Modify the permissions for a specified `delegate` for the specified `node`.

clearRecords(bytes32).notice: Increments the record version associated with an BNS node. May only be called by the owner of that node in the BNS registry.

constructor.notice: L2 Resolver constructor used to establish the necessary contract configuration.

contenthash(bytes32).notice: Returns the contenthash associated with an BNS node.

interfaceImplementer(bytes32,bytes4).notice: Returns the address of a contract that implements the specified interface for this name. If an implementer has not been set for this interfaceID and name, the resolver will query the contract at `addr()`. If `addr()` is set, a contract exists at that address, and that contract implements EIP165 and returns `true` for the specified interfaceID, its address will be returned.

isApprovedFor(address,bytes32,address).notice: Check to see if the `delegate` has been approved by the `owner` for the `node`.

name(bytes32).notice: Returns the name associated with an BNS node, for reverse records. Defined in EIP181.

pubkey(bytes32).notice: Returns the SECP256k1 public key associated with an BNS node. Defined in EIP 619.

setABI(bytes32,uint256,bytes).notice: Sets the ABI associated with an BNS node. Nodes may have one ABI of each content type. To remove an ABI, set it to the empty string.

setAddr(bytes32,address).notice: Sets the address associated with an BNS node. May only be called by the owner of that node in the BNS registry.

setContenthash(bytes32,bytes).notice: Sets the contenthash associated with an BNS node. May only be called by the owner of that node in the BNS registry.

setInterface(bytes32,bytes4,address).notice: Sets an interface associated with a name. Setting the address to 0 restores the default behaviour of querying the contract at `addr()` for interface support.

setName(bytes32,string).notice: Sets the name associated with an BNS node, for reverse records. May only be called by the owner of that node in the BNS registry.

setPubkey(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32).notice: Sets the SECP256k1 public key associated with an BNS node.

setRegistrarController(address).notice: Allows the `owner` to set the registrar controller contract address.

setReverseRegistrar(address).notice: Allows the `owner` to set the reverse registrar contract address.

setText(bytes32,string,string).notice: Sets the text data associated with an BNS node and key. May only be called by the owner of that node in the BNS registry.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: ERC165 compliant signal for interface support.

text(bytes32,string).notice: Returns the text data associated with an BNS node and key.
